DAMATURU – Irked by the deteriorating conditions of some health facilities, Yobe State Governor Mai Mala Buni has approved the complete renovation and expansion of Kumagannam General Hospital, Yusufari Local Government Area, at the cost of N404, 766,929.83. This was contained in a press statement signed by Alhassan Sule Mamudo, Information officer Yobe State Ministry for Local Government and Chieftaincy Affairs made available to Daily Independent in Damaturu on Monday. According to him, work has since Wednesday September 11, 2019, commenced following a meeting of all stakeholders at the site led by the Permanent Secretary Ministry for Local Government and Chieftaincy Affairs, Ibrahim Abba Geidam. “During the meeting, Ibrahim Abba Geidam said they are in the town on the directives of the Governor Yobe State, Mai Mala Buni, after granting approval for the expansion and remodeling of the general hospital”. He said that officials from the Ministry for Local Government, Ministry of Land and Housing, Hospitals Management Board, Yusufari Local Government and the contractors, met at the site and extensively discussed the details of the contract, expectations of the government from the contractors and need for close supervision by the technical team of the Ministry of Land and Housing.